properties.DESCRIPT_1: Built in 1969, Blk 1 Jalan Kukoh used to consist of both a market and food section. After upgrading in 2010, the centre was converted to a food centre with 21 cooked food stalls.

properties.Name: Tanglin Halt Market
properties.DESCRIPT_1: Built way back in 1964, Tanglin Halt Market is an iconic hawker centre within the Tanglin Halt estate. The hawker centre was given a facelift in 2003, and currently comprises 28 cooked food stalls and 89 market stalls.

properties.Name: Tiong Bahru Market
properties.DESCRIPT_1: Located in one of the oldest and most charming neighbourhoods, Tiong Bahru Market was built in 1950 as a single-storey centre.  The centre merged with Blk 84 and 84A Lim Liak Street during the upgrading in 2006, and was converted into a three-storey buil

properties.Name: Beo Crescent Market
properties.DESCRIPT_1: Located near to Tiong Bahru MRT station and PSB Academy, Beo Crescent Market/Food Centre was built in 1965.  The centre serves the mature estate of Havelock and Tiong Bahru area.

properties.Name: Newton Food Centre
properties.DESCRIPT_1: Popular with both locals and tourists alike.  Often rated by foodies as one of the best hawker centres in Singapore, Newton Food Centre is well known for dishes like BBQ Seafood, Hokkien Mee, Po Piah, Satay, Fried Carrot Cake etc.  Extremely crowded duri

properties.Name: Old Airport Road Blk 51 (51 Old Airport Road Food Centre and Shopping Mall)
properties.DESCRIPT_1: The renowned Blk 51 Old Airport Road is famed for its excellent yet affordable food. Built in 1973, it consists of 168 cooked food stalls on the ground level and 54 lock-up stalls on the second level. The large number of cooked food stalls serve up an am

properties.Name: Pasir Panjang Food Centre
properties.DESCRIPT_1: Situated along Pasir Panjang Road and near to industrial estates, the food centre comprises 45 cooked food stalls and serves a variety of hawker fare including BBQ Seafood and Zi Char. Built in 1978.

properties.Name: Aljunied Ave 2 Blk 117 (Blk 117 Aljunied Market and Food Centre)
properties.DESCRIPT_1: Next to Geylang East Swimming Complex and other amenities, the hawker centre caters to the marketing and dining needs of the residents at Geylang East. The centre was built in 1978 and comprises 79 cooked food stalls and 82 market stalls.

properties.Name: Ang Mo Kio Ave 1 Blk 226D (Kebun Baru Market and Food Centre)
properties.ADDRESS_MY: Blk 226D, Ang Mo Kio Ave 1, Singapore 564226
properties.DESCRIPT_1: Located next to a food centre, the hawker centre at Block 226D Ang Mo Kio Ave 1 serves the marketing and dining needs of residents living in the Kebun Baru area. The centre was upgraded in 2010 and consists predominantly of market stalls.

properties.Name: Ang Mo Kio Ave 10 Blk 409 (Teck Ghee Square)
properties.ADDRESS_MY: Blk 409, Ang Mo Kio Ave 10, Singapore 560409
properties.DESCRIPT_1: Also known as Teck Ghee Square, it is one of the three hawker centres that are situated along Ang Mo Kio Ave 10. Built in 1979, the hawker centre comprises 40 cooked food stalls and 148 market stalls.

properties.Name: Ang Mo Kio Ave 4 Blk 628 (Ang Mo Kio 628 Market)
properties.ADDRESS_MY: Blk 628, Ang Mo Kio Ave 4, Singapore 560628
properties.DESCRIPT_1: Originally built in 1979, the hawker centre is located opposite Yio Chu Kang CC and near schools, temples and residential flats.   After the upgrading in 2010, the rebuilt centre consists of  52 cooked food stalls and 166 market stalls to serve the marke

properties.Name: Ang Mo Kio Ave 6 Blk 724 (Blk 724 Ang Mo Kio Market)
properties.ADDRESS_MY: Blk 724, Ang Mo Kio Ave 6, Singapore 560724
properties.DESCRIPT_1: Located conveniently in the heart of the bustling Ang Mo Kio Town Centre, the hawker centre is always packed with patrons, especially during the weekends.  Be prepared to queue for your favourite food at popular stalls!

properties.Name: Ang Mo Kio Street 22 Blk 226H (Kebun Baru Food Centre)
properties.ADDRESS_MY: Blk 226H, Ang Mo Kio Street 22, Singapore 568226
properties.DESCRIPT_1: Commonly known as Kebun Bahru Food Centre, the food centre was built in 1976 to serve the dining needs of Kebun Baru residents. Comprises 29 cooked food stalls.

properties.Name: Bedok Food Centre
